Dikembe Mutombo was elected to the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame on Monday .
Mutombo , a shot-blocking Congolese centre whose finger-wagging motion became one of the most recognized gestures in the game , was a four-times NBA Defensive Player of the Year and led the league in blocked shots for five seasons .
The Mutombo played in the NBA from 1991 until 2009 recording .